I posted to this group a few months back, mentioning that my work site 
had obtained several OS/2 computers, and that I found it, on initial 
inspection, to be buggy and slow.  I think I managed to crash it twice in 
the first week.

Since then, we mostly haven't been using OS/2, booting our "workstations" 
from a DOS floppy because our system administrator has never gotten 
around to obtaining Novell drivers for OS/2.

Also, since then, I have been fooling around with OS/2, and reading this 
newsgroup.  Little by little, I have found that it has become more 
intuitive and interesting to use, especially since I have shed my Windows 
preconceptions about how a GUI "should" behave, and have started to 
remember some of the old conveniences from my Amiga days of years past.

For example, it is simply wonderful to be able to transfer files to and 
from floppies (which I do A LOT) without having to go for a coffee break.

Recently, I read a posting about using a previous version of DOS with 
VMDISK, and I tried it at work.  Now I am able to use our dos NOVELL 
drivers in a DOS window on my OS/2 Desktop, and I have OS/2 up all the 
time at work.  My system administrator was amazed at first, but lately 
he has admitted that he too has been "fooling around" with OS/2 and finds 
it more elegant than Windows.

Anyway, I have become so impressed by OS/2 that I went from a naysayer to 
a supporter, and I'm definitely converting my home system over to it when 
Warp GA comes out.  Microsoft's dragging of the feet hasn't helped their 
cause at all...why should I wait another six months to have long 
filenames?

The moral of the story is that pre-installed OS's are really the way to 
go.  It took me six months to finally come around, but I would have never 
tried OS/2 at all had my job not ordered PS/2s with OS/2 bundled on 
the hard drive.

One question:  Do I have to be a current OS/2 licensee to try out the Beta 
software?  I'm planning on getting the GA anyway, but I really can't wait 
to try out some of the new features.


--jlopez

